@page "/cookies"
@attribute [AllowAnonymous]

<LegalPageShell Title="Cookie notice"
                MetaDescription="How ScamAlert uses cookies and similar technologies on our website."
                CanonicalPath="/cookies">

    <section class="mb-4">
        <h2 class="h5">What we use</h2>
        <p>
            Our website and account portal use cookies and similar technologies (local storage) to keep you signed in, protect against abuse,
            remember cookie consent, and operate the Service securely.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-4">
        <h2 class="h5">Types</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Essential:</strong> authentication session cookies (for example portal sign-in), antiforgery tokens, and consent preferences.</li>
            <li><strong>Functional:</strong> short-lived storage of signup device keys between pages in your browser session.</li>
            <li><strong>Analytics (if enabled):</strong> application telemetry through our hosting provider to diagnose errors and performance.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>We do not use cookies to sell your browsing history to advertisers.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-4">
        <h2 class="h5">Your choices</h2>
        <p>
            Essential cookies are required for account features. You can clear cookies in your browser settings, but you may need to sign in again.
            When we show a cookie banner, accepting it records your choice in browser storage.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-4">
        <h2 class="h5">More information</h2>
        <p>See our <a href="/privacy">privacy policy</a> for how we handle personal data.</p>
    </section>

</LegalPageShell>
